{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a8b6c17-871b-4c54-8f52-f8b028ec0635","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialize, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected automatically via the constructor (MSTest 3.x+)\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    private HttpClient _client;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        // Synchronous init — runs first\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n    }\n\n    // Async init — runs after constructor, before each test\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        _client.Dispose();\n        await ValueTask.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SampleTest()\n    {\n        TestContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_client);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — use for sync setup and `TestContext` injection (no more `[TestInitialize]` needed for simple cases).\n- **`IAsyncInitialize`** — implement `InitializeAsync()` for async setup that runs before each test.\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** / **`IDisposable`** — replaces `[TestCleanup]`.\n- `TestContext` is injected via constructor in MSTest 3.x+ (the property setter pattern still works but constructor injection is preferred).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b65edb83-4fbc-4bfe-994c-c2aba2ac9c43","outputTokens":402,"requestId":"9840:1CF7FE:104C176:148ED5D:69FFE0C1"},"id":"9c3b8873-fba7-4e62-b608-aee61138a911","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:35:06.579Z","parentId":"4035b69e-e09c-4be0-8aec-b1b23f6aceb0"}
